entries.name: PauserRegistry
entries.description: Defines and stores pauser and unpauser roles for EigenLayer contracts and the EigenDAServiceManager.

entries.name: StrategiesBeacon
entries.description: UpgradeableBeacon managing the single implementation for all strategies deployed via StrategyFactory.

entries.name: TokenHopper
entries.description: Minter of the bEIGEN (and thus EIGEN) token. Can execute a predefined payload in predefined intervals (configured by the Owner).

latestPress.description: Timestamp of the latest press. A button-press makes a call (calldata and cooldown are defined by the owner). Anyone can press the button at the defined time intervals.

getHopperConfiguration.description: Current configuration of the TokenHopper, like calldata executed at each button-press (actionGenerator), target (token) and cooldownSeconds.

entries.name: DelegationManager
entries.description: The DelegationManager contract is responsible for registering EigenLayer operators and managing the EigenLayer strategies delegations. The EigenDA StakeRegistry contract reads from the DelegationManager to track the total stake of each EigenDA operator.

receivedPermissions.description: executes scheduled operations after the delay
executes scheduled operations after the delay

entries.name: StrategyFactory
entries.description: Factory contract for permissionless strategy creation via beacon proxies.

entries.name: TimelockControllerBeigen
entries.description: A timelock that allows scheduling calls and executing or cancelling them with a delay.

issuedPermissions.description: executes scheduled operations after the delay

entries.name: RewardsCoordinator
entries.description: Manages the distribution of rewards (arbitrary tokens, EIGEN) to restakers and commission to operators.

transferRestrictionsDisabledAfter.description: Timestamp after which transfer restrictions (whitelist) are disabled. Preset to uint256 max. Restrictions disabled if == 0.

entries.name: StrategyManager
entries.description: The StrategyManager contract is responsible for managing the EigenLayer token strategies. Each EigenDA quorum has at least one strategy that defines the operators quorum stake.

entries.name: RewardAllStakersActionGenerator
entries.description: Generates calldata for the TokenHopper to mint EIGEN and send it to the RewardsCoordinator for distribution to all stakers.

entries.name: TimelockControllerOwning
entries.description: A timelock that allows scheduling calls and executing or cancelling them with a delay.

issuedPermissions.description: executes scheduled operations after the delay

entries.name: StrategyBase
entries.description: A strategy implementation allowing to deposit a specific token as a restakable asset.

values.explanation: Base Strategy implementation to inherit from for more complex implementations

maxPerDeposit.description: Maximum value of one deposit transaction

entries.name: EIGEN token
entries.description: The EIGEN token can be socially forked to slash operators for data withholding attacks (and other intersubjectively attributable faults). EIGEN is a wrapper over a second token, bEIGEN, which will be used solely for intersubjective staking. Forking EIGEN means changing the canonical implementation of the bEIGEN token in the EIGEN token contract.

transferRestrictionsDisabledAfter.description: Timestamp after which transfer restrictions (whitelist) are disabled. Preset to uint256 max. Restrictions disabled if == 0.
